<subSubSection id="758BE484FF8D8D30FF58F6B95D5FD791" pageId="9" pageNumber="752" type="key">
<key id="4900E03EFF8D8D30FF58F6B95D5FD791" pageId="9" pageNumber="752">
<keyStep id="8665AFAAFF8D8D30FF58F6B95C19D700" pageId="9" pageNumber="752">
<paragraph id="3D2EB70FFF8D8D30FF58F6B95D5FD4F9" blockId="9.[201,1322,477,665]" box="[201,1322,477,497]" pageId="9" pageNumber="752">
<keyLead id="8660143AFF8D8D30FF58F6B95D5FD4F9" box="[201,1322,477,497]" pageId="9" pageNumber="752">
1. Leaves with (3)6–7(8) pairs of lateral leaflets and 4–31 interjected leaflets; corollas bluish purple.......... 
<taxonomicName id="FA91CC8CFF8D8D30FB0FF6B95D50D4F8" box="[1182,1317,477,497]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="9" pageNumber="752" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="agrimonifolium">
<emphasis id="0FE56B1DFF8D8D30FB0FF6B95D50D4F8" box="[1182,1317,477,497]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="752">S. agrimonifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D2EB70FFF8D8D30FF58F6915C19D700" blockId="9.[201,1322,477,665]" box="[201,1132,501,521]" pageId="9" pageNumber="752">
<keyLead id="8660143AFF8D8D30FF58F6915C19D700" box="[201,1132,501,521]" pageId="9" pageNumber="752">1. Leaves with (2)3–6(8) pairs of lateral leaflets and 0–6(8) interjected leaflets, corollas white to blue to purple.</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="8665AFAAFF8D8D30FF7BF5695D5CD761" pageId="9" pageNumber="752">
<paragraph id="3D2EB70FFF8D8D30FF7BF5695D5FD731" blockId="9.[201,1322,477,665]" pageId="9" pageNumber="752">
<keyLead id="8660143AFF8D8D30FF7BF5695D5FD731" pageId="9" pageNumber="752">
2. Leaves shiny, glabrous or with scattered 1–2 celled short hairs; fresh seeds greenish with a conspicuous purple spot caused by the purple embryo showing through the seed coat; corollas pure white to blue or purple......... 
<taxonomicName id="FA91CC8CFF8D8D30FB3CF5415D50D730" box="[1197,1317,549,569]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="9" pageNumber="752" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longiconicum">
<emphasis id="0FE56B1DFF8D8D30FB3CF5415D50D730" box="[1197,1317,549,569]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="752">S. longiconicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D2EB70FFF8D8D30FF7BF5595D5CD761" blockId="9.[201,1322,477,665]" pageId="9" pageNumber="752">
<keyLead id="8660143AFF8D8D30FF7BF5595D5CD761" pageId="9" pageNumber="752">2. Leaves not shiny, but finely to coarsely pubescent; fresh seeds greenish throughout and without a spot; corollas typically bluish purple to purple, only rarely white)................................................ 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="8665AFAAFF8D8D30FE9BF5095D5FD791" pageId="9" pageNumber="752">
<paragraph id="3D2EB70FFF8D8D30FE9BF5095D5FD789" blockId="9.[201,1322,477,665]" box="[266,1322,621,641]" pageId="9" pageNumber="752">
<keyLead id="8660143AFF8D8D30FE9BF5095D5FD789" box="[266,1322,621,641]" pageId="9" pageNumber="752">
3. Larger leaves typically 
<quantity id="FA691AEAFF8D8D30FE7CF50A5A4ED789" box="[493,571,621,641]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="752" unit="cm" value="20.0" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="15.0">15–25 cm</quantity>
long, with (3)4–6(8) pairs of lateral leaflets; southeastern Mexico....... 
<taxonomicName id="FA91CC8CFF8D8D30FB2FF5095D50D788" box="[1214,1317,622,641]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="9" pageNumber="752" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oxycarpum">
<emphasis id="0FE56B1DFF8D8D30FB2FF5095D50D788" box="[1214,1317,622,641]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="752">S. oxycarpum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D2EB70FFF8D8D30FE9BF5E15D5FD791" blockId="9.[201,1322,477,665]" box="[266,1322,645,665]" pageId="9" pageNumber="752">
<keyLead id="8660143AFF8D8D30FE9BF5E15D5FD791" box="[266,1322,645,665]" pageId="9" pageNumber="752">
3. Leaves typically 
<quantity id="FA691AEAFF8D8D30FE27F5E25A71D791" box="[438,516,645,665]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.25" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="752" unit="cm" value="32.5" valueMax="40.0" valueMin="25.0">25–40 cm</quantity>
long, with (2)3–5 pairs of lateral leaflets; western Panama............... 
<taxonomicName id="FA91CC8CFF8D8D30FB57F5E15D51D790" box="[1222,1316,645,665]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="9" pageNumber="752" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="woodsonii">
<emphasis id="0FE56B1DFF8D8D30FB57F5E15D51D790" box="[1222,1316,645,665]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="752">S. woodsonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
</key>
